race.comment: CANYA MAYHEM (1) boasts a strong record this journey with five wins and three minors from 11 tries. In the money last time at this track (29.17) in a Special conditions H, finishing a 2.25 lengths second. Appeals as a leading chance in this. TRIBECA (3) could not have been more impressive last start in his lightning 29.16 win at this track over 515m. In form and must include in calculations. COLAC KID (5) has a strong winning strike-rate over this track and trip with four wins and a placing from 10 tries. Comes off a (29.04) win last time, scoring by 2.25 lengths in a Special conditions H over 515m at this track. Looks suited here and can measure up. MEPUNGA TULLY (2) recorded a 1.3 lengths win (29.61) in a Special conditions H last time at this track. Loves this draw, having won three of five starts.
